                           Accessories 2.0

                       Micka‰l Cousin - 1997 May 19th
**********************************************************************


This is a program that allow you, with single TOS, to load accessories
from a directorie of your choice.

So you can keep clean the root of your boot disk and if you use Magic or
Multitos you still have your desk accessories when you have to use single
TOS.

Installation :

Copy ACCS.PRG and ACCS.INF to your AUTO folder and edit the file ACCS.INF
to configure the path of your accessories. If that file is empty or not
here, accessories will be loaded from the \ACCS\ folder.

The path in the configuration file must be like this :
\path\of\the\accessories\     (don't forget the '\' at the end)

This is an exemple :
\SYSTEM\ACCS\

All the accessories will be loaded from this path and be re-loaded after
changing resolutions from the desktop.

